To check, whether an article supports images, simply access Article.getImage().getUrl() which returns a map with the image's url and mime type. Use ImageDownloader.md5(url) to retrieve the image's hash under which it has been saved to disk. Crop the mime type string to find out the appropriate file type. Image mime types follow the convention image/<file type>
